FT  21 MAY 92 / Nissan UK chiefs sent for trial
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TWO SENIOR executives of Nissan UK charged with multi-million-pound tax
evasion were yesterday sent to the Old Bailey for trial.
Mr Michael Hunt, 58, assistant managing director and deputy chairman of the
former importer-distributor of Nissan vehicles, and Mr Frank Shannon, also
58, the company's finance director, are alleged to have cheated the Inland
Revenue out of Pounds 170m.
It is alleged that the money found its way to them after false invoices were
filed for freight payments. Magistrates at Worthing, West Sussex, committed
the men for trial at the Central Criminal Court.
Mr Hunt, of Hove, East Sussex, and Mr Shannon, of Brighton, East Sussex,
were remanded on conditional bail until the trial.
Mr Hunt was granted bail on condition that he lives at his present address
and gives the Inland Revenue 72 hours notice if he travels abroad. He has
also given the court sureties of Pounds 200,000. Mr Shannon was granted bail
on the same conditions and his sureties were worth Pounds 225,000.
