<DOCNO>FT922-6874</DOCNO>
<PROFILE>_AN-CEUBBADYFT</PROFILE>
<DATE>920521
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 92 / World Trade News: Mexico link for Trafalgar
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
TRAFALGAR House Construction, part of the UK property, engineering, shipping
and hotels group, is forming a new company with Sidek of Mexico to take
advantage of the expanding Mexican construction market, writes Andrew
Taylor.
The joint venture based in Guadalajara will begin with a large order book in
the resort development and leisure sector, Trafalgar House said.
The new company, Grupo Sitra, would be able to call on Trafalgar's bigger
technical and operational facilities to work on infrastructure and
industrial projects.
Mr Barry Myers, Trafalgar House director responsible for construction, said
industrial investment in Mexico was expected to rise as North American Free
Trade talks led to reduced trade barriers between the US and Mexico.
</TEXT>
