FT  21 MAY 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The importance of selection in realising better prices for wool was
illustrated at the Goulburn auction in Australia on May 20. Better style
merino fleece of good length and soundness attracted very good competition
and prices moved up by 10 to 30 cents a kg. compared with the previous week.
Otherwise the market was firm. The market indicator rose 6 cents to 588
cents a kg. Offerings in all primary producing markets are declining in
selection and quality at this stage of the season, with drought a
contributory factor leading to lower offerings this season.
