<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 92 / International Capital Markets: Spain launches Ecu250m MTN
issue
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON LONDON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE ALREADY hazy distinction between traditional Eurobonds and medium-term
note issues was further blurred yesterday, when Spain launched Ecu250m
two-year paper under its MTN programme, writes Simon London.
The issue, fully underwritten by Lehman Brothers and the four other dealers
to the programme, is the largest of its type in the Euromarket.
An MTN programme provides a legal framework under which a borrower can issue
bonds in a range of currencies and maturities. MTN issues are normally small
and not underwritten, with dealers placing paper where they can identify
pockets of demand for securities.
However, increasingly large bond issues are being made under the umbrella of
MTN programmes. Until yesterday, the largest issue was a Dollars 153m deal
launched by Eurofima.
