There is good reason for this; Dixons has traditionally remained pretty
quiet about the performance of its 354-store Supasnaps chain which has
proved lacklustre in recent years.
This week, however, the parent company has moved to reshuffle Supasnaps
senior management. Colin Glass, 35, managing director of Supasnaps, has been
elevated to the post of chairman and will also join the Dixons Stores Group
board as marketing director.
'I will be focusing on developing the Dixons and Currys brand propositions
and where they stand on the high street,' he says.
His position at Supasnaps is filled by Elizabeth Fagan, 34, previously
responsible for the company's buying and marketing functions. She joined
Supasnaps from Boots in 1990.
