<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 92 / Azerbaijan may pull out of CIS
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BAKU
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE NEW leadership in Azerbaijan yesterday vowed to take the republic out of
the Commonwealth of Independent States.
Mr Abulfaz Elchibey, leader of the dominant Popular Front and the favourite
candidate to win presidential elections due on June 7, said 'Azerbaijan will
not be part of the current CIS, there is no doubt about that'.
Popular Front leaders refused to accede to a collective security pact signed
by six of the CIS members in Tashkent last week, seeing it as a threat to
the republic's security. They believe Russian influence helped reinstate the
former communist president, Mr Ayaz Mutalibov, for 24 hours last week before
he was forced to flee.
The conflict between Armenian and Azeri forces, which has spread from
Nagorno Karabakh in Azerbaijan to the northern tip of the Azeri autonomous
republic of Nakhichevan within Armenia, is causing growing concern to
neighbouring Turkey and Iran.
</TEXT>
