<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 92 / International Company News: Abitibi-Price sells units to
Alco Standard for CDollars 340m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ABITIBI-PRICE, the Canadian forest products company which is 82 per cent
owned by property developer Olympia &amp; York, has approved the sale of its
printing and industrial paper products distribution businesses to Alco
Standard, the US paper and office products distribution company, for
CDollars 340m (Dollars 284m), Reuters reports.
The four business units involved are Inter City Papers, Barber-Ellis Fine
Papers and Price Daxion in Canada, and Whitaker Carpenter Paper in the US.
Mr Ron Oberlander, president, told a news conference: 'There will be no
special dividend issued from these proceeds.
'These proceeds will go entirely to Abitibi-Price.
'This is part of our announced strategy of selling assets at attractive
prices to strengthen our balance sheet,' Mr Oberlander added.
The deal is expected to be completed in mid to late July and is subject to
the usual investigations by the purchaser and completion of documentation.
</TEXT>
