FT  20 MAY 92 / International Company News: Dayton Hudson profits static
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DAYTON HUDSON, one of the large US retailing groups, yesterday reported
static profits in the three months to May 2, at Dollars 35m, against Dollars
34m, writes Nikki Tait.
Sales, however, rose from Dollars 3.35bn to Dollars 3.72bn, and - assisted
by a relatively upbeat statement from Dayton's chairman, Mr Kenneth Macke -
the shares added Dollars 3 1/4 to Dollars 62 1/4 .
Target, Dayton's discount chain, performed best. Same-store sales rose by 6
per cent and total sales increased from Dollars 1.84bn to Dollars 2.15bn.
Target's operating profits also improved.
