FT  20 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Tuskar Resources recommends offer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The board of Tuskar Resources, the Irish exploration company, yesterday
recommended acceptance of an all-share offer for the company made last March
by Australian exploration company Coplex.
Tuskar's main assets are its exploration licences in the Rubiales and Piriri
oil fields in Colombia. It sold a 54% stake in these to Coplex last month,
in order to finance the completion of a drilling programme, under the terms
of the licence arrangements.
The Coplex bid is a one-for-twelve share-swap offer which values Tuskar at
IPounds 4.67m.
