<HEADLINE>
FT  20 MAY 92 / World Trade News: Disk-drive plant goes to Ireland
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TWO leading disk-drive makers, Matsushita-Kotobuki (MKE) of Japan and
Quantum Corporation of the US, are to open a factory in Ireland as their
European market base, Tim Coone reports from Dublin. MKE makes 40MB to 240MB
hard disk drives in Japan, while Quantum markets them to personal computer
makers. European sales top IPounds 250m (Pounds 227m) a year (35 per cent of
Quantum's world market). The plant should be on stream by autumn.
